09/02/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Following several critical statements about Romania by EU officials, Prime Minister Adrian Nastase said Sunday (8 February) the country's accession negotiations with the EU would continue smoothly. 
EU members have already made the political decision in favour of Romania and the risks have been already overcome, Nastase said. 
He made the statement after attending the meeting of the Socialist International Council in Madrid and after talks with high-raking officials of Spain. 
(Rompres, Mediafax - 09/02/04)
